Add a no-discard lint rule or ESLint helper for Result / ResultAsync.
The biggest safety hole is still this:

saveUser(input) // result ignored
TypeScript will not complain. Errore calls out the same gap. Resultar should have a rule that flags discarded Result / ResultAsync unless explicitly ignored with void.

Standardize expected failures on Error / tagged errors.
Resultar currently allows Err<string> and Err<object>, which is flexible but weak for production observability. I’d keep the generic type, but docs and examples should strongly prefer createTaggedError for domain failures.



